			<!--
			ya, gotcha — your Epic should “fade fast” in Prehistory like Normal/Marathon, keep only clean integer years/turn (≥1), never speed back up, and use 0.5y/turn only at the very end. Here’s a redesigned EPIC (750 turns) block that matches that vibe. Early bands use the same coarse steps as Normal (so it fades quickly), then we add resolution from Classical → Medieval → Renaissance to land exactly at 750.

			Why this fixes the feel:
			- Same early fade as Normal/Marathon. First 7 bands reuse Normal’s 5,000→2,500→1,000→…→125 y/turn steps, so Prehistory isn’t over-detailed.
			- Clean math. Every ≥1y step is an integer; months/turn are all multiples of 12; only the two final bands use 6-month turns.
			- Monotonic. Years/turn never increase as time advances.
			- Pivots line up. 1500/1750/1790/1880/1900/1980/1990/2040/2070/2080/2105 stay intact.
			- Exactly 750 turns. (I checked the sum.)
			-->
